Reminiscent of a&nbsp;painting by an old master, these shot shows&nbsp;dogs and their fleecey wards&nbsp;settling&nbsp;down to the all important business of eating in the snow. The picture&nbsp;was taken at a place called Pass Creek on the top of the Big Horn Mountains in the US state of Wyoming.&nbsp;Heike Blunck who sent it in, snapped it while feeding corn to her Rambouillet flock of sheep, and their guardian dogs. Do you have an image from your natural local surroundings you want to share with readers?&nbsp;If so, you can&nbsp;send it to us&nbsp;using the upload tool on our page, or by emailing us at ecoafrica@dw.com&nbsp;